{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567111"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18935"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18935"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.94,0.02,0.03,0.01,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11669"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112709"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11669"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18935"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94742"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"107"},{"type":"tags","id":"2425"},{"type":"tags","id":"5375"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5655"},{"type":"tags","id":"5669"},{"type":"tags","id":"5671"},{"type":"tags","id":"5675"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11347"},{"type":"tags","id":"11382"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27459"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27464"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46176"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112709","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112709"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman with cellulitis of her left leg refuses intravenous antibiotics despite the medical team\u0027s recommendation. She is alert, oriented, and demonstrates clear understanding of the risks and benefits after detailed discussion. The medical team has explained the potential for progression to severe sepsis and the risk of death without appropriate treatment, but she maintains her decision to decline intravenous therapy citing work commitments. She expresses a preference for oral antibiotics. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate response to this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document refusal and respect patient decision","Request psychiatric assessment","Obtain an Involuntary Treatment Order to treat patient","Contact next of kin to override decision","Insist on admission for intravenous treatment"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edocument refusal and respect patient decision\u003C/strong\u003E. This upholds the ethical principle of patient autonomy while ensuring proper documentation of the informed decision-making process.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect responses are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest psychiatric assessment\u003C/strong\u003E - There is no indication of impaired decision-making capacity requiring psychiatric evaluation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObtain an Involuntary Treatment Order to treat patient\u003C/strong\u003E - Involuntary treatment orders are only appropriate for mental health conditions where the patient lacks capacity; they cannot be used for physical health conditions in a competent patient\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContact next of kin to override decision\u003C/strong\u003E - This violates patient confidentiality and autonomy as the patient has capacity to make decisions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsist on admission for intravenous treatment\u003C/strong\u003E - Forcing treatment on a competent patient who has refused is unethical and potentially illegal\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen a competent patient makes an informed decision to refuse recommended treatment, healthcare providers must respect this choice while documenting the discussion, ensuring patient understanding, and offering alternative options where available.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Patient autonomy is a fundamental ethical principle that respects the right of competent patients to make informed decisions about their healthcare.","Healthcare providers must respect valid treatment refusal even when they disagree with the patient\u0027s decision.","Documentation of informed refusal includes confirming patient capacity and understanding of consequences."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7923912/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94742"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18935"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94742"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-04T08:50:36+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-04T08:51:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11669"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112709"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"posit